    <briefdescription>
<para>A/B firmware boot manager — slot selection, rollback, confirm. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Works with syn_fwimage headers to manage dual firmware slots. Integrates with syn_boot for crash-loop detection.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="par"><title>Boot Flow</title><para><orderedlist>
<listitem><para>Bootloader reads both slot headers</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><ref refid="syn__fwboot_8h_1afa400f2573b5ceca49ad303453c153bd" kindref="member">syn_fwboot_select()</ref> picks the best slot to boot</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>If selected slot is NEW → mark as TESTING before jumping</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Application calls <ref refid="syn__fwboot_8h_1aa63abcc69a5cf468f5fbd6686c0db161" kindref="member">syn_fwboot_confirm()</ref> after healthy startup</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>If boot fails → next boot sees TESTING + unhealthy → rollback</para>
</listitem></orderedlist>
</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="par"><title>Usage</title><para><programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="structSYN__FwBootManager" kindref="compound">SYN_FwBootManager</ref><sp/>mgr;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="syn__fwboot_8c_1a6fc4bd1ee1c8b3d78bb4a0a03337f146" kindref="member">syn_fwboot_init</ref>(&amp;mgr,<sp/>SLOT_A_ADDR,<sp/>SLOT_B_ADDR);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>In<sp/>bootloader:<sp/>pick<sp/>which<sp/>slot<sp/>to<sp/>run</highlight><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">uint8_t<sp/>slot<sp/>=<sp/><ref refid="syn__fwboot_8c_1afa400f2573b5ceca49ad303453c153bd" kindref="member">syn_fwboot_select</ref>(&amp;mgr);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">uint32_t<sp/>entry<sp/>=<sp/><ref refid="syn__fwboot_8h_1acae8e54f4deb559d3b9584081bffb5e6" kindref="member">syn_fwboot_slot_addr</ref>(&amp;mgr,<sp/>slot)</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>+<sp/></highlight><highlight class="keyword">sizeof</highlight><highlight class="normal">(<ref refid="structSYN__FwImageHeader" kindref="compound">SYN_FwImageHeader</ref>);</highlight></codeline>
